{
  "texts": [
    "The first GC method, GCond [26], employs gradient matching as the optimization strategy.",
    "However, the limitations associated with single-step gradient alignment constrain the overall performance of GC.",
    "Therefore, follow-up studies are proposed to explore and enhance the optimization process.",
    "Gradient matching.",
    "CTRL [53] argues that the distance measurement in gradient matching is coarse, which relies on cosine similarity and solely focuses on the directional aspect of gradients."
  ]
}